[[Image:Okres senica.png|thumb|right|350px|Location of [[Senica District]] in the [[Trnava Region]]]]

'''Borský Mikuláš''' is a large [[village]] and [[municipality]] in [[Senica District]] in the [[Trnava Region]] of western [[Slovakia]].

==History==
In [[history|historical records]] the [[village]] was first mentioned in [[1394]]. 

==Geography==
The [[municipality]] lies at an [[altitude]] of 198 [[metres]] and covers an [[area]] of 49.982km². It has a [[population]] of about 3879 people.
 
